South African bank Capitec said on Tuesday it was not aware of any investigation into its loan origination charges. Bloomberg reported that the South African Reserve Bank had asked the National Credit Regulator to launch an investigation into fees charged by Capitec. Read: Sarb calls for Capitec fee probe. Capitec shares fell as much as 5% on the Bloomberg report, which cited an unnamed source, and were trading 4.6% lower at R846.65 at 08:50 GMT. “There is no such thing,” Capitec’s chief financial officer Andre du Plessis told Reuters by telephone. “I have no knowledge of such an investigation being called.”